#: src/kernel/advanced-instructions.md:1
msgid "Advanced Build and Test Instructions"
msgstr "進階建置與測試說明"

#: src/kernel/advanced-instructions.md:3
msgid "User-Mode Unit Tests"
msgstr "使用者模式單元測試"

#: src/kernel/advanced-instructions.md:5
msgid ""
"Asterinas consists of many crates, some of which do not require a VM "
"environment and can be tested with the standard `cargo test`. They are "
"listed in the root `Makefile` and can be tested together through the "
"following Make command."
msgstr ""
"Asterinas 由許多軟體箱組成，其中部分不需要 VM 環境，即可使用標準的 `cargo "
"test` 進行測試。這些軟體箱已列在根目錄的 `Makefile` 中，並可透過以下 Make 命"
"令進行統一測試。"

#: src/kernel/advanced-instructions.md:15
msgid ""
"To test an individual crate, enter the directory of the crate and invoke "
"`cargo test`."
msgstr "若要測試單個軟體箱，請進入該軟體箱的目錄並執行 `cargo test`。"

#: src/kernel/advanced-instructions.md:17
msgid "Kernel-Mode Unit Tests"
msgstr "內核模式單元測試"

#: src/kernel/advanced-instructions.md:19
msgid ""
"Many crates in Asterinas do require a VM environment to be tested. The unit "
"tests for these crates are empowered by OSDK."
msgstr ""
"Asterinas 中的許多軟體箱都需要虛擬機環境才能進行測試。這些軟體箱的單元測試是"
"由 OSDK 提供支援的。"

#: src/kernel/advanced-instructions.md:26
msgid ""
"To test an individual crate in kernel mode, enter the directory of the crate "
"and invoke `cargo osdk test`."
msgstr ""

#: src/kernel/advanced-instructions.md:33
msgid "Integration Test"
msgstr "整合測試"

#: src/kernel/advanced-instructions.md:35
msgid "General Test"
msgstr "一般測試"

#: src/kernel/advanced-instructions.md:37
msgid ""
"The following command builds and runs the test binaries in `test/initramfs/"
"src/apps` directory on Asterinas."
msgstr ""
"以下命令會在 Asterinas 上建置並執行位於 `test/initramfs/src/apps` 目錄中的測"
"試二進位檔。"

#: src/kernel/advanced-instructions.md:43
msgid "Syscall Test"
msgstr "系統呼叫測試"

#: src/kernel/advanced-instructions.md:45
msgid ""
"The following command builds and runs the syscall test binaries on Asterinas."
msgstr ""

#: src/kernel/advanced-instructions.md:51
msgid ""
"To run system call tests interactively, start an instance of Asterinas with "
"the system call tests built and installed."
msgstr ""

#: src/kernel/advanced-instructions.md:57
msgid ""
"Then, in the interactive shell, run the following script to start the "
"syscall tests."
msgstr ""

#: src/kernel/advanced-instructions.md:63
msgid "Debug"
msgstr "除錯"

#: src/kernel/advanced-instructions.md:65
msgid "Using GDB to Debug"
msgstr "使用 GDB 進行除錯"

#: src/kernel/advanced-instructions.md:67
msgid ""
"To debug Asterinas via [QEMU GDB support](https://qemu-project.gitlab.io/"
"qemu/system/gdb.html), you can compile Asterinas in the debug profile, start "
"an Asterinas instance and run the GDB interactive shell in another terminal."
msgstr ""

#: src/kernel/advanced-instructions.md:71
msgid ""
"Start a GDB-enabled VM of Asterinas with OSDK and wait for debugging "
"connection:"
msgstr ""

#: src/kernel/advanced-instructions.md:77
msgid ""
"The server will listen at the default address specified in `Makefile`, i.e., "
"a local TCP port `:1234`. Change the address in `Makefile` for your "
"convenience, and check `cargo osdk run -h` for more details about the "
"address."
msgstr ""

#: src/kernel/advanced-instructions.md:81
msgid "Two options are provided to interact with the debug server."
msgstr ""

#: src/kernel/advanced-instructions.md:83
msgid "A GDB client: start a GDB client in another terminal."
msgstr "GDB 客戶端：在另一個終端機啟動 GDB 客戶端。"

#: src/kernel/advanced-instructions.md:89
msgid ""
"VS Code: [CodeLLDB](https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?"
"itemName=vadimcn.vscode-lldb) extension is required. After starting a debug "
"server with OSDK from the shell with `make gdb_server`, a temporary `launch."
"json` is generated under `.vscode`. Your previous launch configs will be "
"restored after the server is down. Press `F5`(Run and Debug) to start a "
"debug session via VS Code. Click `Continue`(or, press `F5`) at the first "
"break to resume the paused server instance, then it will continue until "
"reaching your first breakpoint."
msgstr ""

#: src/kernel/advanced-instructions.md:97
msgid ""
"Note that if debugging with KVM enabled, you must use hardware assisted "
"breakpoints. See \"hbreak\" in [the GDB manual](https://ftp.gnu.org/old-gnu/"
"Manuals/gdb/html_node/gdb_28.html) for details."
msgstr ""

#: src/kernel/intel-tdx.md:1
msgid "Intel TDX"
msgstr "Intel TDX"

#: src/kernel/intel-tdx.md:3
msgid ""
"Asterinas can serve as a secure guest OS for Intel TDX-protected virtual "
"machines (VMs). This documentation describes how Asterinas can be run and "
"tested easily on a TDX-enabled Intel server."
msgstr ""

#: src/kernel/intel-tdx.md:7
msgid ""
"Intel TDX (Trust Domain Extensions) is a Trusted Execution Environment (TEE) "
"technology that enhances VM security by creating isolated, hardware-enforced "
"trust domains with encrypted memory, secure initialization, and attestation "
"mechanisms. For more information about Intel TDX, jump to the last section."
msgstr ""

#: src/kernel/intel-tdx.md:13
msgid "Why choose Asterinas for Intel TDX"
msgstr ""

#: src/kernel/intel-tdx.md:15
msgid ""
"VM TEEs such as Intel TDX deserve a more secure option for its guest OS than "
"Linux. Linux, with its inherent memory safety issues and large Trusted "
"Computing Base (TCB), has long suffered from security vulnerabilities due to "
"memory safety bugs. Additionally, when Linux is used as the guest kernel "
"inside a VM TEE, it must process untrusted inputs (over 1500 instances in "
"Linux, per Intel's estimation) from the host (via hypercalls, MMIO, and "
"etc.). These untrusted inputs create new attack surfaces that can be "
"exploited through memory safety vulnerabilities, known as Iago attacks."
msgstr ""

#: src/kernel/intel-tdx.md:28
msgid ""
"Asterinas offers greater memory safety than Linux, particularly against Iago "
"attacks. Thanks to its framekernel architecture, the memory safety of "
"Asterinas relies solely on the Asterinas Framework, excluding the safe "
"device drivers built on top of the Asterinas Framework that may handle "
"untrusted inputs from the host. For more information, see [our talk on "
"OC3'24](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3AQ5lpXujGo)."
msgstr ""

#: src/kernel/intel-tdx.md:36
msgid "Prepare the Intel TDX Environment"
msgstr "準備 Intel TDX 環境"

#: src/kernel/intel-tdx.md:38
msgid "Please make sure your server supports Intel TDX."
msgstr "請確保您的伺服器支援 Intel TDX。"

#: src/kernel/intel-tdx.md:40
msgid ""
"See [this guide](https://github.com/canonical/tdx/tree/noble-24.04?"
"tab=readme-ov-file#4-setup-host-os) or other materials to enable Intel TDX "
"in host OS."
msgstr ""

#: src/kernel/intel-tdx.md:43
msgid "To verify the TDX host status, you can type:"
msgstr "若要驗證 TDX 主機狀態，您可以輸入："

#: src/kernel/intel-tdx.md:47
msgid "\"TDX module initialized\""
msgstr ""

#: src/kernel/intel-tdx.md:50
msgid "The following result is an example:"
msgstr ""

#: src/kernel/intel-tdx.md:56
msgid "`TDX module initialized` means TDX module is loaded successfully."
msgstr ""

