msgid ""
"Inside the container, go to the project folder to build and run Asterinas."
msgstr "在容器內，前往專案資料夾建置並執行 Asterinas。"

#: src/kernel/intel-tdx.md:79
msgid "If everything goes well, Asterinas is now up and running inside a TD."
msgstr ""

#: src/kernel/intel-tdx.md:84
msgid ""
"A Trust Domain (TD) is debuggable if its `ATTRIBUTES.DEBUG` bit is 1. In "
"this mode, the host VMM can use Intel TDX module functions to read and "
"modify TD VCPU state and TD private memory, which are not accessible when "
"the TD is non-debuggable."
msgstr ""

#: src/kernel/intel-tdx.md:89
msgid "Start Asterinas in a GDB-enabled TD and wait for debugging connection:"
msgstr ""

#: src/kernel/intel-tdx.md:95
msgid ""
"Behind the scene, this command adds `debug=on` configuration to the QEMU "
"parameters to enable TD debuggable mode."
msgstr ""

#: src/kernel/intel-tdx.md:98
msgid ""
"The server will listen at the default address specified in `Makefile`, i.e., "
"a local TCP port `:1234`."
msgstr ""

#: src/kernel/intel-tdx.md:101
msgid "Start a GDB client in another terminal:"
msgstr ""

#: src/kernel/intel-tdx.md:107
msgid ""
"Note that you must use hardware assisted breakpoints because KVM is enabled "
"when debugging a TD."
msgstr ""

#: src/kernel/intel-tdx.md:110
msgid "About Intel TDX"
msgstr "關於 Intel TDX"

#: src/kernel/intel-tdx.md:112
msgid ""
"Intel® Trust Domain Extensions (Intel® TDX) is Intel's newest confidential "
"computing technology. This hardware-based trusted execution environment "
"(TEE) facilitates the deployment of trust domains (TD), which are hardware-"
"isolated virtual machines (VM) designed to protect sensitive data and "
"applications from unauthorized access."
msgstr ""

#: src/kernel/intel-tdx.md:119
msgid ""
"A CPU-measured Intel TDX module enables Intel TDX. This software module runs "
"in a new CPU Secure Arbitration Mode (SEAM) as a peer virtual machine "
"manager (VMM), and supports TD entry and exit using the existing "
"virtualization infrastructure. The module is hosted in a reserved memory "
"space identified by the SEAM Range Register (SEAMRR)."
msgstr ""

#: src/kernel/intel-tdx.md:127
msgid ""
"Intel TDX uses hardware extensions for managing and encrypting memory and "
"protects both the confidentiality and integrity of the TD CPU state from non-"
"SEAM mode."
msgstr ""

#: src/kernel/intel-tdx.md:131
msgid ""
"Intel TDX uses architectural elements such as SEAM, a shared bit in Guest "
"Physical Address (GPA), secure Extended Page Table (EPT), physical-address-"
"metadata table, Intel® Total Memory Encryption – Multi-Key (Intel® TME-MK), "
"and remote attestation."
msgstr ""

#: src/kernel/intel-tdx.md:138
msgid ""
"Intel TDX ensures data integrity, confidentiality, and authenticity, which "
"empowers engineers and tech professionals to create and maintain secure "
"systems, enhancing trust in virtualized environments."
msgstr ""

#: src/kernel/intel-tdx.md:143
msgid ""
"For more information, please refer to [Intel TDX website](https://www.intel."
"com/content/www/us/en/developer/tools/trust-domain-extensions/overview.html)."
msgstr ""

#: src/kernel/index.md:1
msgid "Asterinas Kernel"
msgstr "Asterinas 內核"

#: src/kernel/index.md:3
msgid "Overview"
msgstr "概覽"

#: src/kernel/index.md:5
msgid ""
"Asterinas is a _secure_, _fast_, and _general-purpose_ OS kernel that "
"provides an _Linux-compatible_ ABI. It can serve as a seamless replacement "
"for Linux while enhancing _memory safety_ and _developer friendliness_."
msgstr ""
"Asterinas 是一款 _安全_ 、 _快速_ 且 _通用_ 的作業系統內核，提供 _相容於 "
"Linux_ 的 ABI。它能作為 Linux 的無縫替代方案，同時提升 _記憶體安全性_ 與 _開"
"發者友善性_ 。"

#: src/kernel/index.md:10
msgid ""
"Asterinas prioritizes memory safety by employing Rust as its sole "
"programming language and limiting the use of _unsafe Rust_ to a clearly "
"defined and minimal Trusted Computing Base (TCB). This innovative approach, "
"known as [the framekernel architecture](the-framekernel-architecture.md), "
"establishes Asterinas as a more secure and dependable kernel option."
msgstr ""

#: src/kernel/index.md:18
msgid ""
"Asterinas surpasses Linux in terms of developer friendliness. It empowers "
"kernel developers to (1) utilize the more productive Rust programming "
"language, (2) leverage a purpose-built toolkit called [OSDK]() to streamline "
"their workflows, and (3) choose between releasing their kernel modules as "
"open source or keeping them proprietary, thanks to the flexibility offered "
"by [MPL](../)."
msgstr ""
"Asterinas 在開發者友善性方面超越了 Linux。它賦予內核開發者以下能力：(1) 使用"
"更具生產力的 Rust 程式語言；(2) 利用名為 [OSDK]() 的專用工具組來簡化工作流"
"程；(3) 由於 [MPL](../) 提供的靈活性，開發者可以自由選擇將其內核模組開源或保"
"持私有。"

#: src/kernel/index.md:26
msgid ""
"While the journey towards a production-grade OS kernel can be challenging, "
"we are steadfastly progressing towards our goal."
msgstr ""

