msgstr ""
"OSDK 支援讓您的作業系統便捷地在 [Intel TDX](https://www.intel.com/content/"
"www/us/en/developer/tools/trust-domain-extensions/overview.html) 環境中執行。"
"Intel TDX 能為您的作業系統提供更安全的環境。"

#: src/osdk/guide/intel-tdx.md:25
msgid ""
"If you see the message \"TDX module initialized\", it means the TDX module "
"has loaded successfully."
msgstr "如果您看到「TDX module initialized」訊息，代表 TDX 模組已成功載入。"

#: src/osdk/guide/intel-tdx.md:28
msgid ""
"The Intel TDX environment requires TDX-enhanced versions of QEMU, KVM, GRUB, "
"and other essential software for running an OS. Therefore, it is recommended "
"to use a Docker image to deploy the environment."
msgstr ""

#: src/osdk/guide/intel-tdx.md:32
msgid "Run a TDX Docker container:"
msgstr ""

#: src/osdk/guide/intel-tdx.md:38
msgid "Edit `OSDK.toml` for Intel TDX support"
msgstr ""

#: src/osdk/guide/intel-tdx.md:40
msgid ""
"As Intel TDX has extra requirements or restrictions for VMs, it demands "
"adjusting the OSDK configurations accordingly. This can be easily achieved "
"with the `scheme` feature of the OSDK, which provides a convenient way to "
"override the default OSDK configurations for a specific environment."
msgstr ""

#: src/osdk/guide/intel-tdx.md:46
msgid ""
"For example, you can append the following TDX-specific scheme to your `OSDK."
"toml` file."
msgstr ""

#: src/osdk/guide/intel-tdx.md:48
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[scheme.\"tdx\"]\n"
"supported_archs = [\"x86_64\"]\n"
"boot.method = \"grub-qcow2\"\n"
"grub.mkrescue_path = \"~/tdx-tools/grub\"\n"
"grub.boot_protocol = \"linux\"\n"
"qemu.args = '''\\\n"
"    -accel kvm \\\n"
"    -m 8G \\\n"
"    -vga none \\\n"
"    -monitor pty \\\n"
"    -nodefaults \\\n"
"    -drive file=target/osdk/asterinas/asterinas.qcow2,if=virtio,format=qcow2 "
"\\\n"
"    -monitor telnet:127.0.0.1:9001,server,nowait \\\n"
"    -bios /root/ovmf/release/OVMF.fd \\\n"
"    -object '{ \\\"qom-type\\\": \\\"tdx-guest\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"tdx0\\"
"\", \\\"sept-ve-disable\\\": true, \\\"quote-generation-socket\\\": { \\"
"\"type\\\": \\\"vsock\\\", \\\"cid\\\": \\\"2\\\", \\\"port\\\": \\\"4050\\"
"\" } }' \\\n"
"    -cpu host,-kvm-steal-time,pmu=off \\\n"
"    -machine q35,kernel-irqchip=split,confidential-guest-support=tdx0 \\\n"
"    -smp 1 \\\n"
"    -nographic \\\n"
"'''\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```toml\n"
"[scheme.\"tdx\"]\n"
"supported_archs = [\"x86_64\"]\n"
"boot.method = \"grub-qcow2\"\n"
"grub.mkrescue_path = \"~/tdx-tools/grub\"\n"
"grub.boot_protocol = \"linux\"\n"
"qemu.args = '''\\\n"
"    -accel kvm \\\n"
"    -m 8G \\\n"
"    -vga none \\\n"
"    -monitor pty \\\n"
"    -nodefaults \\\n"
"    -drive file=target/osdk/asterinas/asterinas.qcow2,if=virtio,format=qcow2 "
"\\\n"
"    -monitor telnet:127.0.0.1:9001,server,nowait \\\n"
"    -bios /root/ovmf/release/OVMF.fd \\\n"
"    -object '{ \\\"qom-type\\\": \\\"tdx-guest\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"tdx0\\"
"\", \\\"sept-ve-disable\\\": true, \\\"quote-generation-socket\\\": { \\"
"\"type\\\": \\\"vsock\\\", \\\"cid\\\": \\\"2\\\", \\\"port\\\": \\\"4050\\"
"\" } }' \\\n"
"    -cpu host,-kvm-steal-time,pmu=off \\\n"
"    -machine q35,kernel-irqchip=split,confidential-guest-support=tdx0 \\\n"
"    -smp 1 \\\n"
"    -nographic \\\n"
"'''\n"
"```"

#: src/osdk/guide/intel-tdx.md:71
msgid ""
"To choose the configurations specified by the TDX scheme over the default "
"ones, add the `--scheme` argument to the build, run, or test command."
msgstr ""
"若要選擇 TDX 方案所指定的組態而非預設組態，請在 build、run 或 test 命令中增"
"添 `--scheme` 引數。"

#: src/osdk/guide/create-project.md:1
msgid "Creating an OS Project"
msgstr "建立作業系統專案"

#: src/osdk/guide/create-project.md:3
msgid ""
"The OSDK can be used to create a new kernel project or a new library "
"project. A kernel project defines the entry point of the kernel and can be "
"run with QEMU. A library project can provide certain OS functionalities and "
"be imported by other OSes."
msgstr ""

#: src/osdk/guide/create-project.md:10
msgid "Creating a new kernel project"
msgstr "建立新的內核專案"

#: src/osdk/guide/create-project.md:12
msgid ""
"Creating a new kernel project is simple. You only need to execute the "
