#: src/to-contribute/index.md:1
msgid "Before You Contribute"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/index.md:3
msgid ""
"This part of the Book provides guidelines for contributing to Asterinas."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/boterinas.md:1
msgid "Boterinas"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/boterinas.md:3
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr "介紹"

#: src/to-contribute/boterinas.md:5
msgid ""
"`@boterinas` is a general-purpose bot designed for a wide variety of tasks "
"in Asterinas. It streamlines maintenance tasks to enhance workflow "
"efficiency."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/boterinas.md:7
msgid ""
"Commands are issued by writing comments that start with the text "
"`@boterinas`. The available commands depend on which repository you are "
"using. The main Asterinas repository contains a `triagebot.toml` file where "
"you can see which features are enabled."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/boterinas.md:9
msgid ""
"Commands for GitHub issues or pull requests should be issued by writing "
"`@boterinas` followed by the command anywhere in the comment. Note that "
"`@boterinas` will ignore commands in Markdown code blocks, inline code "
"spans, or blockquotes. You can enter multiple `@boterinas` commands in a "
"single comment."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/boterinas.md:11
msgid ""
"For example, you can claim an issue and add a label in the same comment."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/boterinas.md:17
msgid ""
"Additionally, `@boterinas` allows for editing comments. If you don't change "
"the text of a command, the edit will be ignored. However, if you modify an "
"existing command or add new ones, those commands will be processed."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/boterinas.md:19
msgid ""
"Below, you'll find a comprehensive guide on how to use `@boterinas` "
"effectively."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/boterinas.md:21
msgid "Commands and Usage"
msgstr "命令與使用"

#: src/to-contribute/boterinas.md:23
msgid "Workflow Management"
msgstr "工作流管理"

#: src/to-contribute/boterinas.md:24
msgid ""
"**`@boterinas rerun`** Restarts the workflow of the current pull request if "
"it has failed unexpectedly. Only the author of the pull request can use this "
"command."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/boterinas.md:27
msgid "Code Review"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/boterinas.md:28
msgid ""
"**`@boterinas codex`** Triggers an AI-powered code review of the pull "
"request using OpenAI Codex. The review posts inline comments highlighting "
"potential issues with correctness, performance, security, and "
"maintainability. Only repository members and collaborators can use this "
"command."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/boterinas.md:31
msgid "Issue and Pull Request Management"
msgstr "議題和拉取請求管理"

#: src/to-contribute/boterinas.md:32
msgid ""
"**`@boterinas claim`**  \n"
"Assigns the issue or pull request to yourself."
msgstr ""
"**`@boterinas claim`**  \n"
"指派議題或拉取請求給你自己。"

#: src/to-contribute/boterinas.md:35
msgid ""
"**`@boterinas release-assignment`**  \n"
"Removes the current assignee from an issue or pull request. This command can "
"only be executed by the current assignee or a team member."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/boterinas.md:38
msgid ""
"**`@boterinas assign @user`**  \n"
"Assigns a specific user to the issue or pull request. Only team members have "
"permission to assign other users."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/boterinas.md:41
msgid "Label Management"
msgstr "標籤管理"

#: src/to-contribute/boterinas.md:42
msgid ""
"**`@boterinas label <label>`**  \n"
"Adds a label to the issue or pull request.  \n"
"_Example:_ `@boterinas label C-enhancement C-rfc`"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/boterinas.md:46
msgid ""
"**`@boterinas label -<label>`**  \n"
"Removes a label from the issue or pull request.  \n"
"_Example:_ `@boterinas label -C-enhancement -C-bug`"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/boterinas.md:50
msgid "Status Indicators"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/boterinas.md:51
msgid ""
"**`@boterinas author`**  \n"
"Indicates that a pull request is waiting on the author. It assigns the `S-"
"waiting-on-author` label and removes both `S-waiting-on-review` and `S-"
"blocked`, if present."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/boterinas.md:54
msgid ""
"**`@boterinas blocked`**  \n"
"Marks a pull request as blocked on something."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/boterinas.md:57
msgid ""
"**`@boterinas ready`**  \n"
"Indicates that a pull request is ready for review. This command can also be "
"invoked with the aliases `@boterinas review` or `@boterinas reviewer`."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/boterinas.md:60
msgid "Notes"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/boterinas.md:61
msgid "Only team members can assign users or remove assignments."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/boterinas.md:62
msgid ""
"Labels are crucial for organizing issues and pull requests, so ensure they "
"are used consistently and accurately."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/boterinas.md:63
msgid ""
"For any issues or questions regarding `@boterinas`, please reach out to the "
"team for support."
msgstr ""

