msgid "Comments and Documentation"
msgstr "註釋與文件"

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/comments-and-documentation.md:3
msgid ""
"API documentation describes API meaning and usage and is rendered by "
"rustdoc. Public APIs should be documented, including crates, modules, "
"structs, traits, functions, and macros. The `#![warn(missing_docs)]` lint "
"helps enforce this baseline."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/comments-and-documentation.md:9
msgid ""
"Asterinas follows Rust community documentation conventions. Two primary "
"references are:"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/comments-and-documentation.md:11
msgid ""
"The rustdoc book: [How to write documentation](https://doc.rust-lang.org/"
"rustdoc/how-to-write-documentation.html)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/comments-and-documentation.md:13
msgid ""
"The Rust RFC book: [API Documentation Conventions](https://rust-lang.github."
"io/rfcs/1574-more-api-documentation-conventions.html#appendix-a-full-"
"conventions-text)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/comments-and-documentation.md:16
msgid "Follow RFC 1574 summary line conventions (`rfc1574-summary`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/comments-and-documentation.md:18
msgid ""
"The first line of a doc comment should be third-person singular present "
"indicative (\"Returns\", \"Creates\", \"Acquires\"), concise, and one "
"sentence."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/comments-and-documentation.md:24
msgid "/// Returns the mapping's start address.\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/comments-and-documentation.md:30
msgid "End sentence comments with punctuation (`comment-punctuation`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/comments-and-documentation.md:32
msgid ""
"If a comment line is a full sentence, end it with proper punctuation. This "
"improves readability in dense code and avoids fragmented prose."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/comments-and-documentation.md:38
msgid ""
"// Good — complete sentence with punctuation.\n"
"// SAFETY: The pointer is derived from a live allocation.\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/comments-and-documentation.md:40
msgid ""
"// Bad — complete sentence without punctuation\n"
"// SAFETY: The pointer is derived from a live allocation\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/comments-and-documentation.md:45
msgid "Wrap identifiers in backticks (`backtick-identifiers`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/comments-and-documentation.md:47
msgid ""
"Type names, method names, and code identifiers in doc comments should be "
"wrapped in backticks for rustdoc rendering. When referring to types, prefer "
"rustdoc links (`[TypeName]`) where possible."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/comments-and-documentation.md:54
msgid ""
"/// Acquires the [`SpinLock`] and returns a guard\n"
"/// that releases the lock on [`Drop`].\n"
"///\n"
"/// Callers must not call `acquire` while holding\n"
"/// a [`RwMutex`] to avoid deadlock.\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/comments-and-documentation.md:62
msgid ""
"Do not disclose implementation details in doc comments (`no-impl-in-docs`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/comments-and-documentation.md:64
msgid ""
"Doc comments should describe _what_ the API does and _how to use it_, not "
"_how it is implemented internally_."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/comments-and-documentation.md:69
msgid ""
"// Good — behavior-oriented\n"
"/// Returns the number of active connections.\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/comments-and-documentation.md:71
msgid ""
"// Bad — leaks implementation details\n"
"/// Returns the length of the internal `HashMap`\n"
"/// that tracks connections by socket address.\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/comments-and-documentation.md:77
msgid "Add module-level documentation for major components (`module-docs`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/comments-and-documentation.md:79
msgid ""
"A module file that serves as an important kernel component (e.g., subsystem "
"entry point, major data structure, driver) should begin with a `//!` comment "
"explaining:"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/comments-and-documentation.md:83
msgid "What the module does"
