#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/select-topics/concurrency-and-races.md:1
msgid "Concurrency and Races"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/select-topics/concurrency-and-races.md:3
msgid ""
"Concurrency code is reviewed with extreme rigor. Lock ordering, atomic "
"correctness, memory ordering, and race condition analysis are all demanded "
"explicitly."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/select-topics/concurrency-and-races.md:7
msgid "Establish and enforce a consistent lock order (`lock-ordering`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/select-topics/concurrency-and-races.md:9
msgid ""
"Acquiring two locks in different orders from different code paths is a "
"potential deadlock. Hierarchical lock order must be established and "
"documented."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/select-topics/concurrency-and-races.md:19
msgid "// Lock order: group of process -> session inner -> job control\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/select-topics/concurrency-and-races.md:25
msgid ""
"See also: PR [\\#2942](https://github.com/asterinas/asterinas/pull/2942)."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/select-topics/concurrency-and-races.md:28
msgid ""
"Never do I/O or blocking operations while holding a spinlock (`no-io-under-"
"spinlock`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/select-topics/concurrency-and-races.md:30
msgid ""
"Holding a spinlock while performing I/O or blocking operations is a deadlock "
"hazard. Use a sleeping mutex or restructure to drop the lock first."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/select-topics/concurrency-and-races.md:36
msgid "// Good — spinlock dropped before I/O\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/select-topics/concurrency-and-races.md:38
#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/select-topics/concurrency-and-races.md:44
msgid "// state: SpinLock<...>\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/select-topics/concurrency-and-races.md:42
msgid "// Bad — I/O while holding spinlock\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/select-topics/concurrency-and-races.md:48
msgid "See also: PR [\\#925](https://github.com/asterinas/asterinas/pull/925)."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/select-topics/concurrency-and-races.md:51
msgid "Do not use atomics casually (`careful-atomics`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/select-topics/concurrency-and-races.md:53
msgid ""
"When multiple atomic fields must be updated in concert, use a lock. Only use "
"atomics when a single value is genuinely independent."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/select-topics/concurrency-and-races.md:59
msgid "// Good — a lock protects correlated fields\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/select-topics/concurrency-and-races.md:67
msgid ""
"// Bad — two atomics that must be consistent\n"
"// but can be observed in an inconsistent state\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/select-topics/concurrency-and-races.md:76
msgid ""
"Critical sections must not be split across lock boundaries (`atomic-critical-"
"sections`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/select-topics/concurrency-and-races.md:78
msgid ""
"Operations that must be atomic (check + conditional action) must happen "
"under the same lock acquisition. Moving a comparison outside the critical "
"region is a correctness bug."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/select-topics/concurrency-and-races.md:85
msgid "// Good — check and action under the same lock\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/select-topics/concurrency-and-races.md:91
msgid ""
"// Bad — TOCTOU race: state can change\n"
"// between the check and the action\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/select-topics/concurrency-and-races.md:101
msgid ""
"See also: PR [\\#2277](https://github.com/asterinas/asterinas/pull/2277)."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/select-topics/defensive-programming.md:1
msgid "Defensive Programming"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/select-topics/defensive-programming.md:3
msgid ""
"Assertions verify invariants that must hold for the program to be correct. "
"Choosing the right assertion type balances safety against runtime cost."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/select-topics/defensive-programming.md:8
msgid "Use `debug_assert` for correctness-only checks (`debug-assert`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/select-topics/defensive-programming.md:10
msgid ""
"Assertions verifying invariants that should never fail in correct code "
"belong in `debug_assert!`, not `assert!`. `debug_assert!` is compiled out in "
"release builds, so the check catches bugs during development without costing "
"anything in production."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/select-topics/defensive-programming.md:22
msgid ""
"See also: [std::debug_assert!](https://doc.rust-lang.org/std/macro."
"debug_assert.html) and [Rust Reference: `debug_assertions`](https://doc.rust-"
"lang.org/reference/conditional-compilation.html#debug_assertions)."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/select-topics/error-handling.md:1
msgid "Error Handling"
msgstr "錯誤處理"

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/select-topics/error-handling.md:3
msgid ""
"Rust's error handling model — `Result`, `?`, and typed errors — is central "
"to writing reliable kernel code."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/select-topics/error-handling.md:6
msgid "Propagate errors with `?` (`propagate-errors`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/select-topics/error-handling.md:8
msgid ""
"Use the `?` operator to propagate errors idiomatically. In kernel code, `."
"unwrap()` is rejected wherever failure is a legitimate possibility."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/select-topics/error-handling.md:15
msgid "// Good — propagate with ?\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/select-topics/error-handling.md:18
msgid "// Bad — unwrap hides the failure path\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/select-topics/error-handling.md:23
msgid ""
"See also: _The Rust Programming Language_, Chapter 9 \"Error Handling\" and "
"[Rust by Example: unpacking options and defaults with `?`](https://doc.rust-"
"lang.org/rust-by-example/std/result/question_mark.html)."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/select-topics/logging.md:1
msgid "Logging"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/select-topics/logging.md:3
msgid ""
"Consistent logging makes debugging tractable across a large kernel codebase."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/select-topics/logging.md:6
msgid "Use `log` crate macros exclusively (`log-crate-only`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/select-topics/logging.md:8
msgid ""
"The project standardizes on the [`log`](https://docs.rs/log) crate's macros: "
"`trace!`, `debug!`, `info!`, `warn!`, `error!`. Custom output functions, "
"`println!`, and hand-rolled serial print macros are not acceptable in "
"production code. Exception: code that runs before the logging subsystem is "
"initialized may use early-boot output helpers."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/select-topics/logging.md:19
#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/select-topics/logging.md:22
msgid "\"VirtIO block device initialized: {} sectors\""
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/select-topics/logging.md:25
msgid "Choose appropriate log levels (`log-levels`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/select-topics/logging.md:27
msgid "Level"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/select-topics/logging.md:27
msgid "Use for"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/select-topics/logging.md:29
msgid "`trace!`"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/select-topics/logging.md:29
msgid "High-frequency events: every interrupt, every packet, every page fault."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/select-topics/logging.md:30
msgid "`debug!`"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/select-topics/logging.md:30
msgid "Development diagnostics: state transitions, intermediate values."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/select-topics/logging.md:31
msgid "`info!`"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/select-topics/logging.md:31
msgid ""
"Rare, noteworthy events: subsystem initialization, configuration changes."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/select-topics/logging.md:32
msgid "`warn!`"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/select-topics/logging.md:32
